                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38049",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=marijn",
                        "name": "marijn",
                        "displayName": "Marijn Huizendveld",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Personally I think this would be the preferred way of declaring the mapping between ActionScript and PHP. I just started using Zend_Amf and I was actually surprised this isn't working already given the notice of method annotations being required.\r\nI'm not familiar with the internals of Zend_Amf so I'm just spitballing here, perhaps a ClassMetaData class should be created that holds the cached class metadata...? A nice example of that can be seen in Doctrine 2",
